      "lesson title": "AI and Regulatory Compliance in Financial Services",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "As artificial intelligence becomes more widely adopted across financial services, regulators are paying closer attention to how firms develop, deploy, and oversee AI-driven systems. This lesson explores why AI introduces unique compliance challenges, including concerns around transparency, accountability, and the potential for bias in automated decision-making. You will learn how existing regulatory frameworks apply to AI, and why supervisory bodies such as the FCA are increasingly focused on ensuring firms can explain and justify the outputs of their AI tools. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of the compliance obligations that come with using AI in a regulated environment, and why getting this right is essential for maintaining trust with both regulators and customers.",
